SENATE RESOLUTION—Expressing appreciation to the staff of
the Senate for their service during the 83rd Session of the
Nevada Legislature.
1 WHEREAS, Each legislative session the Senate elects an officer
2 to serve as the Parliamentarian and Chief Administrative Officer of
3 the Senate; and
4 WHEREAS, The Senate of the 83rd Session of the Nevada
5 Legislature elected Brendan Bucy to serve as Secretary of the
6 Senate for the second time; and
7 WHEREAS, The Secretary of the Senate is responsible for
8 employing all of the staff of the Senate, including the Sergeants at
9 Arms, Front Desk Clerks, Administrative Services Staff, Leadership
10 Officers, Legislative Assistants, Committee Managers, Committee
11 Secretaries and Proofreaders; and
12 WHEREAS, Many of the dedicated members of the staff of the
13 Senate return to work each legislative session, some of whom have
14 retired from other governmental service, bringing a vast amount of
15 knowledge and experience, while others bring talent and expertise
16 from a myriad of diverse backgrounds; and
17 WHEREAS, Throughout the legislative session, the Secretary and
18 staff of the Senate meticulously maintained a thorough and accurate
19 record of all of the proceedings of the Senate and its Committees
20 and diligently ensured that all of the needs of the members of the
21 Senate were met; and
22 WHEREAS, The talented staff who worked for the Senate during
23 the 83rd Session of the Nevada Legislature carried out their
24 responsibilities with ingenuity, enthusiasm and resourcefulness; and
